Plot Lt. David Bradley ( Tom Hanks ) is an American pilot who joins the Royal Air Force ( RAF ) before the United States enters World War II .
After his Boeing B - 17 Flying Fortress bomber is shot down in North Africa , he recovers from a leg injury in Jerusalem .
During his recovery , David meets Sarah Perrara ( Cristina Marsillach ) , a serene girl of Spanish Jewish descent .
The two young people are attracted to each other but she is convinced that their diverse backgrounds mean it could never work .
Her family 's disapproval and the fact that he is a gentile son of a Protestant minister , stand in their way .
Although they keep running into each other in the small community , they find themselves parting as frequently as they find each other .
